In DAG order.

[23:22:59]   - compile: dbt compile generates executable SQL from source model, test, and analysis files.

The compile command is useful for visually inspecting the compiled output of model files. This is useful for validating complex jinja logic or macro usage.

[23:22:59]   - docs: The docs command is responsible for generating your project's documentation website.

[23:22:59]   - list: List the resources in the your dbt project.

[23:22:59]   - parse: The dbt parse command parses and validates the contents of your dbt project. If your project contains Jinja or YAML syntax errors, the command will fail.

